How to Contribute
We welcome contributions from researchers, healthcare professionals, and wellness enthusiasts who are interested in blood sugar regulation. Here’s how you can get involved:

Join the Conversation: Visit the Discussions tab to participate in brainstorming sessions, suggest new research directions, and ask questions.

Submit Research Insights: Have a recent study or article that could contribute to this project? Open an Issue with the title “Research Insight” and provide a summary along with a link.

Collaborate on Existing Findings: Fork the repository, review current findings, and enhance our summaries or documentation. When ready, submit a pull request with your proposed updates.

Propose a Tool or Resource: If you have ideas for practical applications (such as a meal guide or daily habits for blood sugar control), propose them under the Issues tab, tag it as “Tool Proposal,” and outline your concept.
